# 5 Standard Prompt Templates — Claude Code Prompts Reference

> **Usage**: Load when restructuring prompt. Choose appropriate template based on task type.
> Nguồn: Tổng hợp từ research agent dựa trên 7 tool reference (Anthropic, Windsurf, Replit, Perplexity, Lovable, Google/Gemini, Warp.dev)
> Date: 2026-04-17

---

## Template 1: Agent Task Prompt (Multi-file changes)

```xml
<agent_task>
  <identity>
    You are [ROLE], an AI assistant specialized in [DOMAIN].
    Today is ${CURRENT_DATE}.
  </identity>

  <goal>
    [ONE LINE: Primary objective]
  </goal>

  <context>
    <environment>
      Working directory: ${WORKING_DIR}
      OS: ${OS}
      Git status: ${GIT_STATUS}
    </environment>
    <user_info>
      [Relevant user context]
    </user_info>
    <codebase_state>
      [Current file state if relevant]
    </codebase_state>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <must_do>
      - [Required action 1]
      - [Required action 2]
    </must_do>
    <never_do>
      - NEVER [prohibited action 1]
      - NEVER [prohibited action 2]
    </never_do>
    <prefer>
      - DO [recommended approach]
      - AVOID [anti-pattern]
    </prefer>
  </constraints>

  <workflow>
    1. [Step 1]
    2. [Step 2]
    3. [Step 3 - verify]
  </workflow>

  <output_format>
    <changes>
      <change>
        <file>[path]</file>
        <description>[brief change summary]</description>
        <content><![CDATA[
          [Full file content]
        ]]></content>
      </change>
    </changes>
    <verification>
      [How to verify the change]
    </verification>
  </output_format>
</agent_task>
```

**Usage**: Multi-file code generation, feature implementation, refactoring
**Source**: Gemini <changes> structure + Replit proposed_* tags

