## Template 2: Code Review Prompt

```xml
<code_review>
  <goal>
    Review [FILES] for [CRITERIA]
  </goal>

  <review_scope>
    <files_to_review>
      - [file1]
      - [file2]
    </files_to_review>
    <checklist>
      - [ ] Correctness
      - [ ] Security (no secrets, no malicious code)
      - [ ] Performance
      - [ ] Style consistency
      - [ ] Test coverage
    </checklist>
  </review_scope>

  <output_format>
    <verdict type="APPROVE|REQUEST_CHANGES|BLOCK">
      [One line summary]
    </verdict>
    <issues>
      <issue severity="BLOCK|WARN|NIT">
        <location>[file:line]</location>
        <problem>[Description]</problem>
        <suggestion>[How to fix]</suggestion>
      </issue>
    </issues>
    <approved_sections>
      [Files/sections that are good]
    </approved_sections>
  </output_format>

  <restrictions>
    - NEVER approve code with security vulnerabilities
    - NEVER approve code with hardcoded secrets
    - Be constructive, not condescending
  </restrictions>
</code_review>
```

**Usage**: PR review, code quality audit, security check
**Source**: Windsurf section tags + Claude Sonnet tone rules

