## Template 4: Multi-Agent Team Task

```xml
<team_task>
  <team_composition>
    <member name="[agent-1]">
      <role>[role description]</role>
      <responsibility>[what this agent owns]</responsibility>
    </member>
    <member name="[agent-2]">
      <role>[role description]</role>
      <responsibility>[what this agent owns]</responsibility>
    </member>
  </team_composition>

  <task_breakdown>
    <task id="1" owner="[agent-1]" blocked_by="[]">
      [Task description]
      <output>[Expected output format]</output>
    </task>
    <task id="2" owner="[agent-2]" blocked_by="[1]">
      [Task description]
      <output>[Expected output format]</output>
    </task>
  </task_breakdown>

  <coordination>
    <communication>
      - Use SendMessage to communicate between agents
      - Refer to agents by name
      - Mark tasks completed via TaskUpdate
    </communication>
    <quality_gate>
      [What must be verified before moving to next task]
    </quality_gate>
  </coordination>

  <constraints>
    <all_agents>
      - NEVER commit unless explicitly asked
      - Prefer evidence over assumptions
      - Verify before claiming completion
    </all_agents>
  </constraints>
</team_task>
```

**Usage**: Complex multi-step tasks, parallel execution, agent orchestration
**Source**: Claude Code workflow patterns + Replit proposed_* structure

